theorem Topology.interior_diff_subset {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {s t : Set X} :
    (interior s \ closure t) ⊆ interior (s \ t) := by
  intro x hx
  rcases hx with ⟨hx_int_s, hx_not_closure_t⟩
  -- Obtain an open set `U` with `x ∈ U ⊆ s`.
  rcases hx_int_s with ⟨U, hU_open, hxU, hU_subset_s⟩
  -- `x` also lies in the open complement of `closure t`.
  have hx_in_compl : x ∈ (closure t)ᶜ := by
    simpa using hx_not_closure_t
  have hV_open : IsOpen ((closure t)ᶜ) := (isClosed_closure).isOpen_compl
  -- Consider `W = U ∩ (closure t)ᶜ`, an open neighbourhood of `x`.
  have hxW : x ∈ U ∩ (closure t)ᶜ := ⟨hxU, hx_in_compl⟩
  have hW_open : IsOpen (U ∩ (closure t)ᶜ) := IsOpen.inter hU_open hV_open
  -- `W` is contained in `s \ t`.
  have hW_subset : U ∩ (closure t)ᶜ ⊆ s \ t := by
    intro y hy
    have hy_in_s : y ∈ s := hU_subset_s hy.1
    have hy_not_t : y ∉ t := by
      intro hy_t
      exact hy.2 (subset_closure hy_t)
    exact ⟨hy_in_s, hy_not_t⟩
  -- Hence `x` belongs to the interior of `s \ t`.
  exact mem_interior.2 ⟨U ∩ (closure t)ᶜ, hW_open, hxW, hW_subset⟩

theorem Topology.interior_closure_eq_interior_of_isClosed
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} (hA_closed : IsClosed A) :
    interior (closure A) = interior A := by
  simpa [hA_closed.closure_eq]
